you were wanted.

00:57.591 --> 01:00.060
And how much we love you.

01:01.895 --> 01:04.298
You're our baby.

01:05.566 --> 01:09.203
We are just so excited
to meet you.

01:09.237 --> 01:12.740
But I'm getting ahead
of myself here.

01:12.773 --> 01:14.542
I should go back
to the beginning.

01:14.575 --> 01:16.877
See, this fairytale began
in a faraway land called Ohio,

01:16.910 --> 01:18.646
where four
very different people,

01:18.679 --> 01:21.115
against all odds,
ended up becoming a family.

01:21.149 --> 01:23.884
Would you look at that?

01:23.917 --> 01:25.419
Just strutting
down the middle

01:25.453 --> 01:27.321
of Buck Eye Road
in broad daylight,

01:27.355 --> 01:29.123
proud as gay peacocks.

01:29.157 --> 01:31.492
Why shouldn't they be, Nana?
Don't call me that.

01:31.525 --> 01:34.162
I don't look old enough
to be a grandmother.
Great-grandmother.

01:34.195 --> 01:36.930
I happen to love the gays.
I could never get my hair

01:36.964 --> 01:39.433
to look this good
without 'em.
Seems like they
love each other, so...

01:39.467 --> 01:41.302
Oh, and now with the PDA?

01:41.335 --> 01:43.437
