12:32.986 --> 12:34.988
He's making that face
like he needs to go potty.

12:35.022 --> 12:36.056
David, that's you.

12:36.089 --> 12:37.825
He just went.
Well...

12:39.159 --> 12:42.162
Come here. Oh.
Oh, yeah.

12:42.195 --> 12:44.431
He looks like me
when I was a puppy.

12:44.464 --> 12:46.733
(ringtone playing)

12:46.766 --> 12:47.801
It's Gary.

12:47.835 --> 12:49.502
Yes.

12:49.536 --> 12:51.438
Hi, Bryan, it's Gary Snyder,
Expanding Families.

12:51.471 --> 12:53.273
How are you?

12:53.306 --> 12:56.844
I just want to apologize again
for the incident that occurred

12:56.877 --> 12:57.978
with your previous
surrogate choice.

12:58.011 --> 12:59.312
We had no idea.

12:59.346 --> 13:01.681
Celine Dion gave her
a great reference.

13:01.714 --> 13:03.316
Well, we dropped
the litigation

13:03.350 --> 13:04.784
when we found out the womb
terrorist wasn't pregnant.

13:04.818 --> 13:05.919
Well, we have a new surrogate,

13:05.953 --> 13:07.520
and I am absolutely confident

13:07.554 --> 13:09.456
she'd be perfect for your needs.

13:09.489 --> 13:11.658
Why don't you just come in
and meet her?
Please?

13:11.691 --> 13:12.960
I'm great at
being pregnant.

13:12.993 --> 13:14.928
I had tons of energy
and no morning sickness.

13:14.962 --> 13:16.263
Having Shania is the
most successful thing

13:16.296 --> 13:17.597
I've done in my life so far.

13:17.630 --> 13:19.632
Any family history of cancer?
No.

13:19.666 --> 13:22.435
He's a doctor
for lady bits.

13:22.469 --> 13:24.704
A gay-necologist.
Good for you.

13:24.737 --> 13:29.709
So why, then, does a beautiful,
smart, seemingly sane person

13:29.742 --> 13:32.279
want to gestate
someone else's child?

13:32.312 --> 13:35.648
Well, $35,000 is a
huge chunk of money.

13:35.682 --> 13:38.151
I need a way to change
my daughter's life.

13:38.185 --> 13:39.953
I want to go to
law school someday.

13:39.987 --> 13:41.688
And you have no problem
with doing this for two men?

13:41.721 --> 13:43.857
Oh, no, I requested
a gay couple.

13:43.891 --> 13:47.627
I was driving, and I overheard
a deranged homeless woman

13:47.660 --> 13:49.296
saying not so nice things

13:49.329 --> 13:52.966
about a lesbian couple,
but all I could think was,

13:53.000 --> 13:54.567
a family is a family.

13:55.869 --> 13:57.370
And love is love.

14:00.207 --> 14:01.875
I love that Goldie.
I don't know.

14:01.909 --> 14:03.310
She reminds me of me

14:03.343 --> 14:04.878
when I first came
to L.A. to make it.

14:04.912 --> 14:06.713
I did like
that daughter of hers.

14:06.746 --> 14:08.048
I'm less sold on her.

14:08.081 --> 14:09.082
(laughs)

14:09.116 --> 14:11.351
I want us to have a baby.

14:11.384 --> 14:13.820
At some point, we just got
to move past the setbacks.

14:13.853 --> 14:16.689
So, what's stopping you?

14:16.723 --> 14:19.026
I don't know.

14:19.059 --> 14:21.694
I don't want our sperm
to be competitive.

14:21.728 --> 14:24.197
I don't want our sperm

14:24.231 --> 14:26.900
to do some crazy
genetic race.

14:26.934 --> 14:28.501
What are you talking about?

14:28.535 --> 14:32.372
When did you make
this decision?

14:32.405 --> 14:36.343
I have four masculine brothers
and one masculine sister.

14:36.376 --> 14:37.377
(laughs)

14:37.410 --> 14:39.446
You're an only child.

14:39.479 --> 14:42.082
It's more important for
you to create something

14:42.115 --> 14:44.851
that's yours biologically
to recognize.

14:44.884 --> 14:46.886
Not being the
baby's bio dad

14:46.920 --> 14:48.922
doesn't make me
any less of a dad.

14:48.956 --> 14:50.723
You'd do that for me?

14:50.757 --> 14:53.693
No, for me.

14:53.726 --> 14:56.329
We need more people like you
walking around in the world.

14:58.098 --> 14:59.599
Plus, then I'll get to
lord it over you forever.

14:59.632 --> 15:00.767
Thank you.

15:01.468 --> 15:02.769
I love you.

15:02.802 --> 15:04.404
I love you.

15:04.437 --> 15:06.073
Now, go make me
macaroni and cheese

15:06.106 --> 15:07.440
so we can get started
on my foot rub.

15:07.474 --> 15:10.043
(groans)
Okay.

15:10.077 --> 15:12.445
Thank you.

15:20.988 --> 15:23.256
Your embryos are ready
for implantation.

15:23.290 --> 15:25.492
Now, as a doctor, David
has indicated he'd like

15:25.525 --> 15:27.727
to witness the procedure if
that's okay with you, Goldie.

15:27.760 --> 15:30.097
Sure. He'll be more
involved than the dad was

15:30.130 --> 15:32.065
last time I got pregnant.

15:32.099 --> 15:33.466
I'd love you to be
there, too, Bryan.

15:33.500 --> 15:35.135
Oh, no, no, I faint
at the sight of vagina.

15:35.168 --> 15:36.636
They're like
tarantula faces.

15:36.669 --> 15:39.072
Oh.
Can my daughter stay with me?

15:39.106 --> 15:40.507
Oh, no, honey, don't you
worry about anything.

15:40.540 --> 15:41.841
I'll watch
your little cutie here.

15:41.874 --> 15:42.976
You just go get yourself
knocked up.

15:43.010 --> 15:45.145
Me and Lady Pants
will chill out.

15:47.347 --> 15:48.648
Do everything I wouldn't do.

15:56.623 --> 15:59.192
These pants were
very expensive.

15:59.226 --> 16:02.495
To me, they don't look
like that.

16:02.529 --> 16:04.531
Any second thoughts?

16:04.564 --> 16:06.033
I'm good.

16:06.066 --> 16:07.300
How about you?

16:07.334 --> 16:09.269
Oh, me?
Yeah.

16:09.302 --> 16:11.138
I mean, having a baby
is a huge step.

16:11.171 --> 16:13.606
Everything in your life
is gonna be covered

16:13.640 --> 16:15.875
in poop, spit-up and drool.

16:15.908 --> 16:18.811
It'll be a bit like living
with my soon-to-be-ex-husband.

16:18.845 --> 16:20.513
(laughs)

16:20.547 --> 16:22.482
Oh, my God,
you're crying.

16:22.515 --> 16:24.651
I'm always the guy that
everyone counts on.

16:24.684 --> 16:26.619
I mean, when do I get
a chance to fall apart?

16:26.653 --> 16:28.488
Well, now is
a real good time.

16:28.521 --> 16:30.790
At work I'm a rock,
and at home I'm a rock.

16:30.823 --> 16:32.025
I'm like what
Simon and Garfunkel

16:32.059 --> 16:33.393
would refer to
as an island.

16:33.426 --> 16:34.694
Are those the doctors
you work with?

16:34.727 --> 16:35.728
Oh, my God.

16:37.497 --> 16:38.865
(sniffs)
You know, I've delivered

16:38.898 --> 16:40.333
a thousand babies
in my life,

16:40.367 --> 16:41.634
and I don't think
I've ever held one

16:41.668 --> 16:43.703
that's over four
minutes old.

16:45.838 --> 16:47.507
What if I'm not
ready to be a dad?

16:47.540 --> 16:50.243
I became a mom
in a Rite Aid bathroom.

16:50.277 --> 16:52.612
I had to borrow 25 cents
to get into the stall.

16:53.946 --> 16:55.182
You're way ahead
of the game.

16:55.215 --> 16:56.816
David,

16:56.849 --> 17:00.553
you are going to be
an amazing dad.

17:01.688 --> 17:03.490
(door opens)

17:03.523 --> 17:05.325
WOMAN: Excuse me.
Someone's here for you.

17:05.358 --> 17:07.694
Claims not to
be your nana.

17:07.727 --> 17:09.862
How... how'd you find me?

17:09.896 --> 17:12.265
I have been hot
on your trail for days.

17:12.299 --> 17:13.866
This one led me
straight to you.

17:13.900 --> 17:16.569
They're in Venice Beach,
California.

17:16.603 --> 17:18.371
Twitter stamped their location.

17:18.405 --> 17:21.508
You people are so darn
good with computers.

17:21.541 --> 17:24.211
And thanks for helping
build the railroads.

17:24.244 --> 17:25.445
Who cares how?

17:25.478 --> 17:26.679
There is a giant

17:26.713 --> 17:28.181
homosexual elephant
in the room.

17:28.215 --> 17:30.283
Listen, ma'am,
I know it's a lot

17:30.317 --> 17:31.718
to digest,
but my partner and I

17:31.751 --> 17:32.752
cannot have a child

17:32.785 --> 17:34.121
the traditional way,

17:34.154 --> 17:36.723
and Goldie here wants
to carry ours for us.

17:36.756 --> 17:38.291
Oh, Bryan, I hauled my ass

17:38.325 --> 17:40.860
all the way across town
to bring you these damn eggs.

17:40.893 --> 17:42.195
Oh, no.

17:42.229 --> 17:45.532
You are not growing
one of her kind of eggs

17:45.565 --> 17:46.866
in my granddaughter.

17:46.899 --> 17:48.301
Oh, no, sweetie,
these are poached.

17:48.335 --> 17:50.603
What the hell you mean,
my kind of eggs?

17:50.637 --> 17:52.972
The last time I checked,
this diamond-speckled watch

17:53.005 --> 17:54.541
my gay boss bought me

17:54.574 --> 17:57.644
without his consent,
it was 2012.

17:57.677 --> 17:59.812
Now, why don't you take your
Callista Gingrich hairdo

17:59.846 --> 18:02.749
and your racist mind
back to the past

18:02.782 --> 18:04.484
or the South
where they belong?

18:04.517 --> 18:06.786
Nana, I want to
help this family.

18:06.819 --> 18:08.421
I feel like I just ate
a black and gay stew

18:08.455 --> 18:09.956
right before
I fell asleep.

18:09.989 --> 18:12.091
This is a nightmare.
No,

18:12.125 --> 18:13.393
this ain't a nightmare,
but I'm gonna

18:13.426 --> 18:15.094
pinch you real
good to make sure.

18:15.128 --> 18:17.497
Goldie, have you lost
your damn mind?

18:17.530 --> 18:19.432
What are you doing, helping
these salami-smokers?

18:19.466 --> 18:21.668
Wow.
That's a good one. That's new.

18:21.701 --> 18:23.903
It is so wrong,
and have you even thought

18:23.936 --> 18:26.773
about what kind of message
you are sending your daughter?

18:26.806 --> 18:28.608
That you can be
whatever you want to be

18:28.641 --> 18:30.477
no matter how many people
tell you that you're nothing.

18:30.510 --> 18:32.179
It is not normal.

18:32.212 --> 18:34.447
The baby I want to carry for
David and Bryan will have

18:34.481 --> 18:36.783
two loving parents who
desperately want a child.

18:36.816 --> 18:38.785
Who are you to say
that's not normal?

18:38.818 --> 18:40.187
Because I lived it.

18:42.655 --> 18:46.426
Okay, here goes.

18:46.459 --> 18:48.495
Your grandfather had a friend
who worked for him

18:48.528 --> 18:50.330
at the pet store for many years.

18:50.363 --> 18:52.131
Uncle Leon, with
all the puffy hair?

18:52.165 --> 18:54.601
One day, my old Chrysler leaked
oil all over my driveway,

18:54.634 --> 18:57.604
so I had to go down
to the pet store and get a bag

18:57.637 --> 18:59.306
of kitty litter
to soak it up.

18:59.339 --> 19:03.042
I walked through the back door,
and I saw them together.

19:03.075 --> 19:05.011
Oh, Nana.

19:05.044 --> 19:07.514
Leon stood there
with his private parts dangling

19:07.547 --> 19:09.949
for all the parakeets
to laugh at.

19:09.982 --> 19:12.319
What the hell
is she talking about?

19:12.352 --> 19:14.821
That man didn't love me.
So, what did you do?

19:14.854 --> 19:16.456
I stayed with him
for ten more years,

19:16.489 --> 19:18.191
and I helped him build
his Beanie Baby collection.

19:18.225 --> 19:22.161
Now, Goldie,
I am begging you, please,

19:22.195 --> 19:23.296
let's just go get Goggles

19:23.330 --> 19:25.498
and get back in the car
and go home.

19:25.532 --> 19:26.966
I'm sorry, Nana.

19:26.999 --> 19:29.035
We're staying.

19:29.068 --> 19:32.071
I need to help these
guys... and myself.

19:41.180 --> 19:43.049
(mouthing)

19:52.124 --> 19:54.494
Goldie's mama ran away
and ditched her with me

19:54.527 --> 19:56.596
when she was just
eight years old.

19:56.629 --> 19:59.532
Three generations
of babies raising babies.

19:59.566 --> 20:00.900
Earlier, when you referred

20:00.933 --> 20:02.402
to the homosexual elephant
in the room,

20:02.435 --> 20:04.571
you were talking
about David, right?

20:06.573 --> 20:09.542
Okay, we are here waiting
to find out if we made you.

20:09.576 --> 20:11.578
I'm so excited,
I haven't eaten in two days.

20:11.611 --> 20:13.946
Thanks to you,
I'm wearing my skinny jeans.

20:13.980 --> 20:15.682
Does it say
anything yet?

20:15.715 --> 20:17.049
Remember,
one line-- not pregnant,

20:17.083 --> 20:18.418
two lines-- pregnant.

20:18.451 --> 20:19.719
GOLDIE:
I just peed. I'm waiting.

20:19.752 --> 20:21.087
Say something
to the baby, Daddy David.

20:21.120 --> 20:22.389
What, what, what...?
Come on.

20:22.422 --> 20:23.723
We don't know
anything yet.

20:23.756 --> 20:25.425
(indistinct chatter)
(Bryan gasps)

20:25.458 --> 20:27.627
BRYAN:
And there's the lady
who made you possible.

20:27.660 --> 20:30.430
Hi. This is the longest
three minutes of my life.

20:30.463 --> 20:32.031
Oh, now's the perfect time
for the thing.

20:32.064 --> 20:32.799
Oh, the thing.
Get the thing.

20:32.832 --> 20:33.900
One second.

20:33.933 --> 20:35.568
What?

20:35.602 --> 20:37.537
Yes, come here.

20:37.570 --> 20:39.272
(grunts)

20:39.306 --> 20:41.474
Guys.

20:41.508 --> 20:43.276
It's your lawyer suit.
I helped pick it.

20:43.310 --> 20:44.444
BRYAN:
And then I re-picked it

20:44.477 --> 20:46.413
with far fewer feathers
and bangles.

20:46.446 --> 20:48.548
We want to help make
your dreams come true.

20:48.581 --> 20:50.983
'Cause you're helping us
with ours.

20:51.017 --> 20:54.587
But what if it
doesn't work?

20:54.621 --> 20:56.289
What if that stick
says I'm not pregnant?

20:56.323 --> 20:58.090
Honey, it doesn't matter
what it says.

20:58.124 --> 21:00.460
This whole thing only started
feeling real after we met you.

21:00.493 --> 21:02.629
You gave us...

21:03.663 --> 21:05.965
You gave me hope.

21:07.166 --> 21:08.801
Now I know how to be a dad.

21:08.835 --> 21:10.069
The only question is: when?

21:10.102 --> 21:13.039
Now, what the hell
does that stick say?

